The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Calcutta University decided on Thursday to reschedule the dates of undergraduate examinations slated from May 4 because of the Lok Sabha elections. There will be no change in exam dates till April 30. The revised schedule will be announced on Friday, a senior university official said.     Metro Railway will run trains from 11.30am on a trial basis on two Sundays  March 22 and 29  officials said on Thursday. The trains will run at an interval of 10 minutes between 11.30am and 2pm and at 15-minute intervals from then on till 9.45pm. If there are enough passengers, the revised schedule will be implemented permanently. At present, Metro operations begin at 2pm on Sundays.     Three men were found critically injured on the road near Bagha Jatin flyover late on Thursday evening. A motorcycle was found nearby. The trio were admitted to Peerless Hospital. Police suspect they were hit by another vehicle.     An unidentified man in his 30s was knocked down by a speeding minibus on the Howrah-Shibtala route at the Calcutta end of Howrah bridge on Thursday. He was taken to Medical College and Hospital, where he was declared dead. The bus driver fled.    A minibus on the Howrah-Naktala route overturned near the Park Street crossing opposite Metro Bhavan at 10.30pm on Thursday. Witnesses said the driver lost control after he swerved to avoid hitting two youths who had come in front of the bus. Two passengers were taken to SSKM Hospital with minor injuries. The driver and conductor of the bus fled.    Around 300 casual and contract workers of Calcutta Tramways Company were arrested on Rani Rashmoni Avenue for trying to breach a police cordon on Thursday afternoon. The police said the workers, under the banner of CTC Bus Driver-O-Karmachari Samiti, took out a procession from Raja Subodh Mullick Square at 3pm to protest departmental irregularities.     Goutam Das, a 25-year-old help of a truck, was injured on Thursday after the speeding vehicle overturned near Galiff Street, pinning him under it. Police said the driver fled. Firefighters and cops rescued Das and took him to RG Kar hospital with a fractured leg. He was later transferred to CMRI Hospital.     Fifty-six students of the West Bengal Madrasah Students Union were arrested for putting up a roadblock at Dorina crossing on Thursday afternoon. They had taken out a procession from Alliah University near Haji Mohammad Mohsin Square and marched towards Maidan protesting the state governments education policies.     Four students were injured after members of the SFI and the Trinamul Congress Chhatra Parishad clashed on Thursday at Netaji Subhas Engineering College in Garia. First-year students of the Trinamul camp had allegedly passed offensive comments at Debasis Barman, the head of the Basic Engineering Sciences department, after he asked them to attend classes. SFI-affiliated students retaliated, leading to the scuffle. The injured were admitted to hospital. The SFI members lodged a police complaint. The college authorities said classes would be not held on Friday.     A fire broke out in an apartment in Mandirtala in Howrah on Thursday at 3.30pm. Two fire tenders took 30 minutes to douse the flames. No one was injured.             
